quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,When the sky bursts open
  84,2,and obeys its Lord as it must
  84,3,when the earth flattens out
  84,4,and casts out all that is within it and becomes empty
  84,5,and obeys its Lord as it must
  84,6,"O man, having striven hard towards your Lord, you shall meet Him"
  84,7,he who is given his record in his right hand
  84,8,shall have an easy reckoning
  84,9,"and he shall return to his people, joyfully"
  84,10,but as for him whose record shall be given to him from behind his back
  84,11,he will pray for utter destruction
  84,12,and he will enter the blazing flame
  84,13,He used to be happy with his own people
  84,14,"for he never thought that he would have to return [to God]"
  84,15,But he will indeed! His Lord was ever watching him
  84,16,I swear by the glow of sunset
  84,17,by the night and what it covers
  84,18,and the moon when it grows full
  84,19,you will progress from stage to stage
  84,20,What is wrong with them that they do not believe
  84,21,"When the Quran is read to them, why do they not fall to their knees"
  84,22,"Indeed, those who are bent on denying the truth reject it"
  84,23,God is quite aware of what they are storing in their hearts
  84,24,"Therefore, give them the news of a painful punishment"
  84,25,But for those who believe and do good works; for them there shall be a never-ending reward
  85,1,By the sky with its constellations
  85,2,and by the promised Day
  85,3,by the Witness and the witnessed
  85,4,destroyed were the people of the trench
  85,5,the makers of the fuel-stoked fire
  85,6,They sat by it
  85,7,to watch what they were doing to the believers
  85,8,"whom they hated for no other reason than that they believed in God, the Almighty, the Praiseworthy"
  85,9,to whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. God is witness over all things
  85,10,"Those who persecute the believing men and believing women, and then do not repent, will surely suffer the punishment of Hell, and the torment of burning"
  85,11,But those who believe and do good deeds shall be rewarded with gardens watered by flowing rivers. That is the supreme triumph
  85,12,The grip of your Lord is indeed severe
  85,13,"it is He who begins and repeats [His creation]"
  85,14,and He is the Forgiving and Loving One
  85,15,The Lord of the Glorious Throne
  85,16,Executor of His own will
  85,17,Have you not heard the story of the hosts
  85,18,of Pharaoh and Thamud
  85,19,Yet those who deny the truth persist in denial
  85,20,God encompasses them from all sides
  85,21,It is indeed a glorious Quran
  85,22,written on a preserved Tablet
  86,1,By the heavens and that which comes in the night
  86,2,and what could make you know what it is that comes in the night
  86,3,It is the shining star
  86,4,"[for] no human being has been left unguarded"
  86,5,Let man reflect on what he was created from
  86,6,He was created from spurting fluid
  86,7,issuing from between the backbone and the breastbone
  86,8,He certainly has the power to bring him back to life
  86,9,On the Day when secrets are disclosed
  86,10,"[man] will have no power, and no helper"
  86,11,"By the heavens, ever-revolving"
  86,12,by the earth cracking open with new growth
  86,13,It is surely a decisive utterance
  86,14,and is not to be taken lightly
  86,15,They are planning a scheme
  86,16,and so am I
  86,17,"so bear with those who deny the truth, and let them be for a little while"